enty around Torbay and the site is lucky enough\nto have a relatively  secluded beach just 10 minutes walk down the hill,\nideal for swimming or just relaxing and taking in the 'rays '.\n\nThe campsite consists of two fields, Back field - Sites 1 to 8b **\nFront field Sites 9 16\nThe back field has a wood pile & 2 water points,\nthe front field also has a wood pile & 3 water points\n\nThere is also a Fridge \/ Freezer room available for all campers\n(Free of charge). There are hot showers available (20p) as are\nthe usual washing toilet and water facilities.\n\nWe have a hall with brand new large kitchen to hire\n\nDuring the summer season there is a tuck \/ gift shop on site\nrun by volunteers for your sweet tooth, and for the 'knotty' people\namongst you there are some pioneering poles available.\n\nPublic fields and wood surround the campsite providing an\nexcellent location for group wide games.\n\nThe site has a small chapel and campfire circle both of which\ncan be used by visiting groups, the service team will also organized a\nweekly campfire for any visiting groups that may be interested.","contact":"bookingmanager@torbay-scout-campsite.co.uk","link":"http:\/\/home.btconnect.com\/torbayscouts\/","lastupdated":"2012-10-14","latitude":"50.493590","longitude":"-3.518570","categoryid":"1"},{"facilityid":"176","title":"Consall Scout Camp","description":"The Camp is situated in the heart of the Staffordshire Moorlands, between Leek and Cheadle. It has excellent access to many local facilities, including Alton Towers (10 miles away), the Peak District and the Potteries.","contact":"Graham Alcock52, Shirburn road,Leek.ST13 6LE\nTel 01538 383525","link":"http:\/\/www.consallscoutcamp.co.uk","lastupdated":"2012-02-26","latitude":"53.023949","longitude":"-2.031990","categoryid":"1"},{"facilityid":"177","title":"Hunters Greave Campsite","description":"","contact":"","link":"","lastupdated":"2012-01-11","latitude":"53.825654","longitude":"-1.630670","categoryid":"1"},{"